descriptionHtml:
-----Project Explanation------
Okay i don\'t you guys know if I\'ve been working on a mod called \"Assassin gear\" on a thread under mods. This project was my first complete set from Skyrim so there many bumps along the road. After struggling to get everything like I wanted, I finally just need to take a break from it and do another project or something. I will come back to this to finish fix all small problems but its most like not going to happen for a another week or two. Everything Is well enough to use so I decided to release an Alpha Version.


Updates:
Alpha1: Recreated the mesh so the mid weight shouldn\'t get deformed as much.


Fixs to do:
-Texture clean up/ texture the white armor pieces
-fix the seams
-finished creating snow white texture


----Actually Project----
Body Used: Custom Body, made off CBBE/CHSBHC

Description:
This is a light set armor that i used by Coreborn Agents to take down there opponents. The leather is bound together by magicka making hexagon patterns and hold the suit together along the seams.

Obtaining:
-Craft at Forge (Under Misc)

Both Files contain the Bodysuit, Armored Version, Gloves, and Boots

Two Verions:
regular version-works with anything
BBP- have to have Cherry\'s CHSHC mod installed (skeleton/animations)


----FAQ---

Q:Are you going to update the BBP version
A: I am no longer supporting BBP as it\'s hassle to make sure it work and it like break randomly. I\'ll see if i cant figure out these problems I have, but its not my main priority.

Q:How come you used custom body and not CBBE or another famous one?
A:I can use whatever body I want, these mods are made for myself I just happen to share them

Q: I don\'t like X or Y can you fix that?
A: Sorry buddy your gonna have fix that yourself. I\'ve made list of what I plan to fix, I\'m not adding more.

Q:Can you convert this another body type?
A: No, if you want another body type version, you can make it
